{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=November 2018}} {{Infobox book | name = Rabindra Chitravali | title_orig = | translator = | image = | caption = | author = [[R. Siva Kumar]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = India | language = English | series = | subject = Rabindranath Tagore's Paintings and Philosophy of Art | genre = Art | publisher = Pratikshan | pub_date = 2011 | english_pub_date = | pages = 1600+ | isbn = 978-81-89323-30-1 | oclc = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }} '''''Rabindra Chitravali''''' is a 2011 four-volume set of books by art historian [[R. Siva Kumar]] that contains paintings of [[Rabindranth Tagore]]. These include about 1700 paintings in the Rabindra Bhavana and [[Kala Bhavana]] collections of [[Visva-Bharati]], [[Santiniketan]]; and more than 300 paintings in the collection of the [[National Gallery of Modern Art]] and the collections at Rabindra Bharati University, Kolkata; [[National Gallery of Modern Art]], New Delhi and Bangalore; and [[Indian Museum]], Kolkata.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pratikshanbooks.com/booksonart/rabindra_chitravali.html |title= Pratikshan :: Rabindra Chitravali |publisher=Pratikshanbooks.com |date= |accessdate=2013-08-12}}</ref><ref name="hindustantimes1">{{cite web |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/India/Tagore-paintings-glow-on-his-150th-birth-anniversary/Article1-541584.aspx |title=Tagore paintings glow on his 150th birth anniversary |publisher=''Hindustan Times'' |date=2010-05-10 |accessdate=2013-08-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130421080810/http://www.hindustantimes.com/News-Feed/India/Tagore-paintings-glow-on-his-150th-birth-anniversary/Article1-541584.aspx |archivedate=2013-04-21 |df= }}</ref>
==Significance== R. Siva Kumar said that reproducing the works in print was important in making them accessible to the public, as "The ink used in the originals is not very durable. The paintings can’t be left in the open for long".<ref name="hindustantimes1"/>
In a review for the [[Royal Asiatic Society]], [[Cambridge Journals]], W. Andrew Robinson called the reproductions of "unparalleled quality" and said the four volumes cover almost all of Tagore's existing work, though some works are missing.<ref>[http://andrew-robinson.org/uploads/REVIEW_OF_PAINTINGS_OF_TAGORE.pdf Review of Book]by Andrew Robinson, Royal Asiatic Society {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131217224721/http://andrew-robinson.org/uploads/REVIEW_OF_PAINTINGS_OF_TAGORE.pdf# |date=17 December 2013 }}</ref>
==See also== *''[[The Last Harvest: Paintings of Rabindranath Tagore]]'' *''[[Santiniketan: The Making of a Contextual Modernism]]''
